1
00:01:26,080 --> 00:01:27,000
Zhiyuan.

2
00:01:35,880 --> 00:01:37,039
Zhiyuan.

3
00:01:40,160 --> 00:01:41,240
Yingzi.

4
00:01:42,280 --> 00:01:43,039
Zhiyuan.

5
00:01:43,039 --> 00:01:43,880
Yingzi.

6
00:01:46,479 --> 00:01:48,440
Where's the child?

7
00:01:49,560 --> 00:01:50,360
The child...

8
00:01:52,360 --> 00:01:56,560
We got separated while fleeing.

9
00:01:57,840 --> 00:01:59,900
The child is with your older brother.

10
00:02:03,760 --> 00:02:06,360
How did you find this place?

11
00:02:09,120 --> 00:02:10,759
Our home is gone.

12
00:02:13,240 --> 00:02:16,040
Now there is war all over China.

13
00:02:19,680 --> 00:02:23,240
I could only ask around and search along the way,

14
00:02:23,840 --> 00:02:25,280
looking for the transport team,

15
00:02:25,280 --> 00:02:26,240
looking for you.

16
00:02:32,640 --> 00:02:34,680
It was chaos and war all the way.

17
00:02:37,440 --> 00:02:39,040
It must have been hard on you.

18
00:02:41,079 --> 00:02:42,360
I told myself,

19
00:02:43,560 --> 00:02:45,360
if I still couldn't find you,

20
00:02:46,440 --> 00:02:48,040
I would go back to Nanyang.

21
00:02:50,760 --> 00:02:53,690
Did you receive the letter your brother wrote to you?

22
00:02:56,480 --> 00:02:58,840
I received the letter.

23
00:03:00,320 --> 00:03:02,320
Then why didn't you reply?

24
00:03:04,840 --> 00:03:08,320
Do you know how hard it was waiting for you?

25
00:03:08,320 --> 00:03:10,120
Why didn't you reply?

26
00:03:30,440 --> 00:03:31,240
Assemble!

27
00:03:39,680 --> 00:03:40,480
Today,

28
00:03:41,240 --> 00:03:42,970
the supplies we are delivering

29
00:03:43,040 --> 00:03:45,100
are more important than ever before.

30
00:03:45,320 --> 00:03:48,780
So we must carefully deliver these supplies to the front line.

31
00:03:49,560 --> 00:03:51,160
The soldiers on the front line

32
00:03:51,160 --> 00:03:53,480
are waiting for these medicines to save their lives.

33
00:03:53,480 --> 00:03:54,360
Understood?

34
00:03:54,360 --> 00:03:55,280
Understood.

35
00:03:56,440 --> 00:03:57,370
Get in the truck.

36
00:04:02,440 --> 00:04:04,200
We have to go from there.

37
00:04:04,200 --> 00:04:05,160
Let's see.

38
00:04:05,160 --> 00:04:05,800
Let me think.

39
00:04:05,800 --> 00:04:07,000
That's a long detour.

40
00:04:07,640 --> 00:04:08,120
We can only detour from here.

41
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:08,650
Zhiyuan.

42
00:04:09,360 --> 00:04:11,840
Zhiyuan, your letter.

43
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:12,520
It's been so long.

44
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:13,840
We haven't received any letters.

45
00:04:13,840 --> 00:04:15,560
What does your letter say?

46
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:17,200
Let's look together.

47
00:04:23,280 --> 00:04:24,210
Second Brother,

48
00:04:24,760 --> 00:04:26,090
Father has passed away.

49
00:04:26,440 --> 00:04:29,480
He wasn't able to see you one last time before his death.

50
00:04:29,480 --> 00:04:30,680
He left with regrets.

51
00:04:31,280 --> 00:04:32,920
Now that our country is in peril,

52
00:04:32,920 --> 00:04:36,120
I know your spirit of serving the country is commendable.

53
00:04:36,120 --> 00:04:39,560
But I hope you can return home and join me in sending Father off on his final journey.

54
00:04:39,560 --> 00:04:40,680
If you do not return,

55
00:04:40,680 --> 00:04:43,080
I'm afraid you will be called an unfilial son by future generations.

56
00:04:43,080 --> 00:04:45,080
And I will find it hard to forgive you.

57
00:04:45,080 --> 00:04:46,010
Hope you return.

58
00:05:14,120 --> 00:05:15,880
I am unfilial.

59
00:05:18,200 --> 00:05:20,000
I couldn't fulfill my filial duties,

60
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:22,200
and send you off on your final journey.

61
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:30,520
But right now,

62
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:34,720
our country is in peril.

63
00:05:36,520 --> 00:05:38,159
I can only

64
00:05:38,159 --> 00:05:40,400
put the country before our family.

65
00:05:42,200 --> 00:05:44,320
May your soul in heaven

66
00:05:46,280 --> 00:05:48,800
bless our transport to be smooth.

67
00:05:51,400 --> 00:05:52,920
I am here,

68
00:05:54,400 --> 00:05:56,880
bowing to you.

69
00:06:32,840 --> 00:06:34,320
Yaoyao, can you hold this for me?

70
00:06:34,320 --> 00:06:36,280
This story is so touching.

71
00:06:39,880 --> 00:06:41,940
A man's knees are as precious as gold.

72
00:06:42,280 --> 00:06:43,320
You are kneeling

73
00:06:43,320 --> 00:06:45,450
for the righteous cause of the nation.

74
00:06:45,880 --> 00:06:47,320
When the country is about to perish,

75
00:06:47,320 --> 00:06:48,580
the roots will be lost,

76
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:50,530
and people are going to die.

77
00:06:50,960 --> 00:06:53,159
Do not forget the ancestral teachings.

78
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:57,880
Azu.

79
00:06:57,880 --> 00:06:58,640
Azu.

80
00:06:59,240 --> 00:07:00,000
Come here.

81
00:07:03,480 --> 00:07:04,810
What's wrong, Grandpa?

82
00:07:09,520 --> 00:07:11,050
Our country is in peril now.

83
00:07:12,080 --> 00:07:14,240
The whole Nanyang is promoting

84
00:07:14,240 --> 00:07:16,320
saving the nation from Japanese aggression.

85
00:07:16,320 --> 00:07:17,360
What do you think

86
00:07:17,360 --> 00:07:18,200
about this?

87
00:07:19,560 --> 00:07:21,200
Grandpa,

88
00:07:21,200 --> 00:07:22,120
If the roots are cut,

89
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:23,450
the leaves will wither.

90
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:26,200
The fundraising in Nanyang is so enthusiastic

91
00:07:26,280 --> 00:07:27,280
because

92
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:29,810
the roots of us overseas Chinese are in China.

93
00:07:31,240 --> 00:07:32,880
If they want to destroy China,

94
00:07:32,880 --> 00:07:34,000
they must first ask if the millions of

95
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:36,680
overseas Chinese in Nanyang will agree.

96
00:07:40,400 --> 00:07:42,640
These Japanese invaders burn, kill, and loot,

97
00:07:42,640 --> 00:07:43,770
stopping at no evil.

98
00:07:44,120 --> 00:07:45,720
It is simply intolerable.

99
00:07:46,640 --> 00:07:48,170
If we don't take action now,

100
00:07:48,320 --> 00:07:49,520
where is the justice?

101
00:07:50,400 --> 00:07:51,720
My grandson,

102
00:07:51,720 --> 00:07:53,600
well said about justice!

103
00:07:55,120 --> 00:07:57,040
Those words you just said

104
00:07:57,040 --> 00:07:58,240
make you a true man.

105
00:08:00,560 --> 00:08:01,360
Azu,

106
00:08:02,120 --> 00:08:03,520
now that you are an adult,

107
00:08:04,640 --> 00:08:06,040
I won't keep anything

108
00:08:06,040 --> 00:08:07,120
from you anymore.

109
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:10,160
There is one thing

110
00:08:10,160 --> 00:08:11,960
I have decided for you.

111
00:08:12,440 --> 00:08:13,440
Tell me, Grandpa.

112
00:08:13,920 --> 00:08:15,640
I am sending you back to China.

113
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:17,800
Sending me back to China?

114
00:08:18,520 --> 00:08:19,960
To fight the enemy.

115
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:23,160
If it weren't for

116
00:08:23,160 --> 00:08:24,320
my old age,

117
00:08:25,520 --> 00:08:26,360
I would definitely

118
00:08:26,360 --> 00:08:28,240
kill them all myself.

119
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:30,160
Grandpa,

120
00:08:30,160 --> 00:08:31,000
to be honest,

121
00:08:31,480 --> 00:08:35,200
I have already signed up for the anti-Japanese activities back home.

122
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:37,280
It's just...

123
00:08:37,280 --> 00:08:38,640
I'm worried about you.

124
00:08:40,520 --> 00:08:42,320
You don't need to worry about me.

125
00:08:42,840 --> 00:08:45,300
I have already discussed it with Uncle Tang.

126
00:08:45,720 --> 00:08:47,000
After you return,

127
00:08:47,120 --> 00:08:48,780
we will look after each other.

128
00:08:50,040 --> 00:08:52,120
It's a pity

129
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:53,850
that they only have daughters.

130
00:08:54,840 --> 00:08:58,100
Otherwise, I would have asked one of them to accompany you.

131
00:08:59,240 --> 00:09:00,040
Grandpa.

132
00:09:01,240 --> 00:09:02,120
Follow me.

133
00:09:25,560 --> 00:09:27,240
Ancestors above,

134
00:09:28,040 --> 00:09:29,640
our country is in peril.

135
00:09:31,040 --> 00:09:32,640
I, Qiantang, have decided to send

136
00:09:32,640 --> 00:09:35,320
my grandson Lin Yaozu back to fight in the war.

137
00:09:36,640 --> 00:09:39,240
May the ancestors protect Yaozu

138
00:09:39,240 --> 00:09:40,320
and keep him safe.

139
00:09:58,040 --> 00:09:59,320
The whole country,

140
00:09:59,960 --> 00:10:01,240
the old, the weak, women, and children,

141
00:10:01,240 --> 00:10:02,280
are all fighting.

142
00:10:03,520 --> 00:10:04,800
Our Lin family

143
00:10:04,800 --> 00:10:05,680
has no cowards.

144
00:10:06,480 --> 00:10:07,810
Rest assured, Grandpa.

145
00:10:07,920 --> 00:10:11,240
Yaozu will definitely keep our ancestors' teachings in mind.

146
00:10:11,240 --> 00:10:13,240
The country is in chaos now,

147
00:10:13,760 --> 00:10:15,160
not like here in Nanyang.

148
00:10:16,040 --> 00:10:17,500
You must keep a low profile

149
00:10:18,440 --> 00:10:19,970
and be careful everywhere.

150
00:10:21,280 --> 00:10:22,080
I understand.

151
00:10:25,320 --> 00:10:27,160
Tonight is New Year's Eve.

152
00:10:27,160 --> 00:10:29,760
Uncle Tang will come over to celebrate with us.

153
00:10:30,120 --> 00:10:32,240
Our two families will have a good meal,

154
00:10:32,240 --> 00:10:35,040
which will also serve as a farewell dinner for you.

155
00:10:37,680 --> 00:10:38,920
Grandpa,

156
00:10:39,280 --> 00:10:40,240
rest assured,

157
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:42,640
I will definitely come back safely.

158
00:10:46,280 --> 00:10:46,810
Let's go.

159
00:11:06,720 --> 00:11:07,840
Grandpa.

160
00:11:07,840 --> 00:11:09,560
Why do we have to make the lantern ourselves?

161
00:11:09,560 --> 00:11:11,560
That's my childhood memory.

162
00:11:12,040 --> 00:11:14,970
Were you also afraid of the dark when you were little?

163
00:11:15,040 --> 00:11:16,640
Who isn't afraid of the dark?

164
00:11:16,880 --> 00:11:18,440
But with a lantern,

165
00:11:18,440 --> 00:11:19,570
you won't be afraid.

166
00:11:20,240 --> 00:11:21,520
Knowing the way back,

167
00:11:22,040 --> 00:11:23,520
you can find your home.
